<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1410,1939]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,327,1487,1513]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[335,591,1488,1513]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophomilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albicosta">
<emphasis box="[335,591,1488,1513]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Lophomilia albicosta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[609,697,1488,1514]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 24" captionStartId="7.[151,274,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[190,1381,229,1740]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,199,1759]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 24. Lophomilia spp., adults. 17. L. kogii, male, Russia, Primorye terr. Khasansky distr., Andreevka (FNM); 18. L. albicosta, male, China, Tapai-Shan (ZFMK); 19. L. albistria, male, Nepal, Kathmandu, Pulchouki Mt. (ZSM); 20. L. albistria, female, Nepal, Pulchouki Mt. (ZSM); 21. L. kobesi, male, holotype, Indonesia, Sumatra (ZSM); 22. L. kobesi, female, paratype, Indonesia, Sumatra (ZSM); 23. L. violescens, holotype, male, Nepal, Godavari (after Yoshimoto, 1993); 24. Hepatica anceps, syntype, Russia, “ Sutschan ” (MNHU)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274661/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Fig. 
<number box="[666,697,1488,1514]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
) can be recognized by the dark brownish-grey forewing with darker streaks between veins in submedial field; wingpattern expressed by contrasting wide yellowish-cream band along costa and one wide cream area with brown transversal postmedial line. Wingspan 
<quantity box="[1268,1400,1565,1591]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.85" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="28.5" valueMax="29.0" valueMin="28.0">28–29 mm</quantity>
. In male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[337,425,1604,1630]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 39" captionStartId="17.[151,269,1781,1805]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,197,1756]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,197,1757]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 39. Lophomilia spp. and Hepatica anceps, adults and male genitalia. 33. L. striatipurpurea, imago (after Holloway 1976); 34. L. striatipurpurea, male genitalia (after Holloway 1976); 35. L. albicosta, China, Tapaishan, prep. 2093 VK ZFMK; 36. L. kobesi, holotype, prep. 6540 GB, Indonesia, Sumatra (ZSM); 37. L. violescens, holotype, Nepal (after Yoshimoto 1993); 38. L. albistria, prep. 6526 GB, Nepal, Kathmandu, Pulchouki Mt. (ZSM); 39. Hepatica anceps, Russia, Primorye terr. prep. AM ZISP." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274664/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Fig. 
<number box="[394,425,1604,1630]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="35.0">35</number>
</figureCitation>
) all structures slender, uncus short, pointed, juxta narrow, deeply cleft basally, wide and plate-like medially; valva with parallel costal and ventral margins; costa not separated from membranous valva; sacculus small, saccular extension thin and weak; clasper fused with costa at the base, directed longitudinally; harpe thin, weak, slightly curved at apex. Aedeagus rather thin, with long coecum; vesica bulbous, with two diverticula, one armed with a patch of short cornuti. Female not examined.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1410,1939]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,514,1797,1823]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Distribution and Biology.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[531,619,1797,1823]" captionStart="FIGURES 50 – 57" captionStartId="19.[151,269,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[192,1387,194,1943]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,194,1948]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 50 – 57. Lophomilia spp., distribution maps. 50. L. flaviplaga; 51. L. takao; 52. L. polybapta; 53. L. nekrasovi; 54. L. rustica; 55. L. hoenei; 56. L. kogii; 57. L. albicosta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274666/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Fig. 
<number box="[586,619,1797,1823]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="57.0">57</number>
</figureCitation>
). Cental 
<collectingCountry box="[726,799,1797,1823]" name="Nepal" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, Central 
<collectingCountry box="[906,980,1797,1823]" name="China" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">China</collectingCountry>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[1045,1096,1797,1823]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">type</typeStatus>
specimens were collected in April (
<date box="[230,343,1836,1862]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1992-04-04">
<number box="[230,246,1836,1862]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="4.0">4</number>
.iv. 
<number box="[278,343,1836,1862]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</date>
), June (
<date box="[435,563,1836,1862]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1936-06-29">
<number box="[435,467,1836,1862]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="29.0">29</number>
.vi. 
<number box="[499,563,1836,1862]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1936.0">1936</number>
</date>
) and August (
<date box="[732,875,1836,1862]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1991-08-17">
<number box="[732,761,1836,1862]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="17.0">17</number>
.viii. 
<number box="[813,875,1836,1862]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</date>
) at elevations of 
<quantity box="[1081,1244,1836,1862]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="m" value="1150.0" valueMax="1300.0" valueMin="1000.0">1000–1300 m</quantity>
in the Godavari village and Mt. Phulchouki near Kathmandu. Probably bivoltine, with adults occuring in hillside forest. The species is reported here from 
<collectingCountry box="[497,567,1913,1939]" name="China" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">China</collectingCountry>
for the first time.
</paragraph>
